                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.512/54: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 19, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Your 93, October 5 noon and 101, Oct. 13, 11 a.m. After further
                    consideration, Department feels that you would be justified, if necessary, in
                    calling the attention of the Bolivian Government to the last paragraph of
                    article 3 of the treaty of 1858 and requesting that American citizens in Bolivia
                    be exempted from payment of the war tax.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
